{"word":"H5992 - עַמִּינָדָב - ʻAmmîynâdâb - am-mee-naw-dawb' - Amminadab","slug":"H5992","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">עַמִּינָדָב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʻAmmîynâdâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>am-mee-naw-dawb'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Amminadab"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>עמּינדב</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>‛ammı̂ynâdâb</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>am-mee-naw-dawb'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Amminadab = \"my kinsman is noble\" <ol><li>son of Ram or Aram and father of Nahshon or Naasson and an ancestor of Jesus; father-in-law of Aaron</li><li>a Kohathite Levite and chief of the sons of Uzziel</li><li>a Levite, son of Kohath; also 'Izhar'</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H5971\">H5971</a> and <a href=\"#/H5068\">H5068</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5971\">H5971</a>, <a href=\"#/H5973\">H5973</a>, <a href=\"#/H5978\">H5978</a>, <a href=\"#/H5980\">H5980</a>, <a href=\"#/H5981\">H5981</a>, <a href=\"#/H5983\">H5983</a>, <a href=\"#/H5984\">H5984</a>, <a href=\"#/H5985\">H5985</a>, <a href=\"#/H5988\">H5988</a>, <a href=\"#/H5989\">H5989</a>, <a href=\"#/H5990\">H5990</a>, <a href=\"#/H5991\">H5991</a>, <a href=\"#/H5996\">H5996</a>, <a href=\"#/H6005\">H6005</a>"}]}